{"key":"processedPost-9672386","value":{"id":9672386,"first":9671623,"last":9674104,"when":1232845029,"utime":"01/25/09 02:57 AM","cleanedPost":"The series 1 from FP is a great filter.&nbsp; I've had mine since he first started making them.&nbsp; You can do large spawn bags, but you'll have to lay them on their sides and do one at a time, because that's all it has room for.&nbsp; If you can afford it, a 24 X 24 will allow you to do ten or more at once, because you can have them open while standing up.&nbsp; Since your PC only holds two, the 12 X 24 will work fine.&nbsp; Don't forget to use a pre-filter.&nbsp; I have since new, and am still on the original HEPA after just over ten years.<br />I can stack 8 large folded spawn bags in front of the filter to cool, and then open one at a time in front of the hood.&nbsp; If I'm doing more than that, I stick them inside tyvek coveralls and zip them up.&nbsp; Tie the sleeves and legs with knots and fold the hood into the zipper and you can leave them there for a week or more and be safe, especially if you PC them with tyvek sleeves inside the way I show in the sawdust/woodchip section on the DVD.<br />RR<br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/05-23/838197699-flow_hood_003a.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/05-23/838197699-thumb_flow_hood_003a.jpg\"></a>"}}